HEADWORD: Distillable
<hw>Dis*till"a*ble</hw> <pr>(d⟦icr⟧s*t⟦icr⟧l"⟦adot⟧*b'l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Capable of being distilled;
especially, capable of being distilled without chemical change or
decomposition; <as>as, alcohol is <ex>distillable</ex>; olive oil is not
<ex>distillable</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

